ould be at \r\n-           least 64MB. This value can be expressed in bytes, or as '64M', '1G' etc.\r\n+           -XX:MaxPermSize=<xx>M. Set or increase this value as necessary: Eucalyptus overrides \r\n+           the standard java default of 64MB to 256MB, you'll likely need to set it to 384MB or higher.\r\n+\t   This value can be expressed in bytes, or as '384M', '1G' etc.\r\n         2) Restart the cloud application.\r\n         3) If this condition continues despite a high value for --XX:MaxPermSize, it may be \r\n            necessary to add more physical memory to the machine.\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nRestarting Eucalyptus cluster controller:\r\n/usr/share/eucalyptus/faults/en_US//1005.xml:47: parser error : Opening and ending tag mismatch: xx line 41 and message\r\n      </message>  \r\n                ^ \r\n/usr/share/eucalyptus/faults/en_US//1005.xml:48: parser error : Opening and ending tag mismatch: message line 39 and resolution\r\n    </resolution> \r\n                 ^\r\n/usr/share/eucalyptus/faults/en_US//1005.xml:49: parser error : Opening and ending tag mismatch: resolution line 38 and fault\r\n  </fault>\r\n          ^\r\n/usr/share/eucalyptus/faults/en_US//1005.xml:50: parser error : Opening and ending tag mismatch: fault line 22 and eucafaults\r\n</eucafaults>\r\n             ^\r\n/usr/share/eucalyptus/faults/en_US//1005.xml:51: parser error : Premature end of data in tag eucafaults line 21\r\n\r\n^\r\n{code}","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"On CC restart, failure parsing fault 1005.xml","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=viglesias","name":"viglesias","key":"viglesias","accountId":"557058:49b276ff-ebf9-4dd6-ada3-b568a2898707","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/5608e